frus:attachment.p:
2. The Allied Authorities reserve the right:
(a) to take such measures as may be necessary for the maintenance of security, [the preservation of democratic government],We believe this phrase is sufficiently covered elsewhere and could therefore be deleted here. the fulfillment of the international obligations and interests of their Governments, or the preservation of the economic and financial stability of Berlin;
(b) to act and legislate for the protection, prestige and security of the Allied forces, their dependents, employees and representatives, their immunities satisfaction of occ costs, and their other requirements.
